 and government policy are keys to Negro employment, with the union dragging its feet in supporting an increased number of black over-the-road drivers. A final section compares the situations in the four industries and forecasts future Negro employment trends in light of the most recent employment data, occupational needs, governmental policy, and other significant factors.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aAfrican AmericansxEmployment. 0aTransport workerszUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Transportation.2bisacsh  aBusiness.  aEconomics.  aPublic Policy.1 aChernish, William N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJeffress, Philip W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJr., Howard W. Risher,, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeone, Richard D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeone, Richard D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorthrup, Herbert R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRisher, Howard W., Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThieblot, Armand J., Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z97831104425260 cprintz978081227632940uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781512821116?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512821116423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781512821116/original  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBK